# Cursor Test Case Maintenance

For any bug fix, hardening change, or new feature that affects model behavior, provider routing, request/response mapping, tool calls, streaming, reasoning, vision, caching, or log diagnostics, update the manual Cursor test cases under `.cursor/test-cases/` before committing.

## When to add or update a test case

Update `.cursor/test-cases/` when a change touches any of these areas:

- Model/provider behavior for Azure OpenAI, Azure Anthropic, DeepSeek, Kimi, MiniMax, or any future provider
- Tool calls, tool outputs, tool definitions, `tool_choice`, or built-in Responses tools
- Streaming SSE mapping, terminal events, `[DONE]` behavior, or finish reasons
- Request body sanitizers, parameter allowlists, normalizers, or format adapters
- KV/cache behavior such as `previous_response_id`, reasoning cache, Claude thinking cache, or image cache
- Model ID routing, model discovery, public/bare model name mapping, or provider inference
- Vercel log diagnostics used to validate production behavior

## Required test case contents

Every manual Cursor test case must include:

- Provider and model route to select in Cursor
- Preconditions, including deployment/env assumptions
- Exact prompt text to paste into Cursor
- Expected Cursor-visible behavior
- Expected file/content changes when relevant
- Expected Vercel log event titles and key fields
- Negative signs that indicate the bug still exists
- Cleanup steps if the prompt creates files

Keep prompts deterministic and low-risk. Prefer tiny files under `.cursor/tmp/` for apply/edit tests.

## Log title contract

When a test case relies on production logs, use stable event titles such as `REQ`, `RES`, `TOOLS_SHAPE`, `TOOLS_FIXED`, `AZURE_STREAM_SUMMARY`, `INPUT_CHAIN`, `MESSAGES_TO_INPUT`, `PREV_RESP_ID_FOUND`, and `PREV_RESP_ID_MISS`.

Do not change existing log event titles casually. If a new diagnostic is required, add a clean uppercase event title and document it in the related test case.

## If Cursor cannot exercise the path

If the path cannot be triggered from Cursor UI, still add a test case entry that says so and include the closest local replay command or production-log verification method. Do not leave the test-case folder stale just because the verification is not fully manual.
